filterdata = filter(data, Year == 2018 & City == "Ames")
names(filterdata) <- make.names(names(filterdata))
sumdaydata = filterdata %>% group_by(Month,Day) %>% summarize(Sales=sum(Sale..Dollars.))
ggplot(sumdaydata, aes(x=Day,y=Sales, color=Month)) + geom_point() + facet_wrap(sumdaydata$Month)

By observing the two plots, it is easy to see that every Friday/Saturday liqour sales increase dramatically. Even during the dates of the football games, there seems to be a standard increase in sales and volume sold. I thought there would be more of a drastic increase during games, but that doesnt seem to be the case. I guess that the lure of a football game doesnt bring that drastric of an increase in sales to the liqour market here in ames. I have a feeling that this is because the people who travel here to see the games buy their alcohol elsewhere before arriving.
